Package runner

Class ShiftedSpikeScatterPlotRunner

java.lang.Object
org.jzy3d.analysis.AbstractAnalysis
runner.ScatterPlot
runner.ShiftedSpikeScatterPlotRunner
All Implemented Interfaces:
org.jzy3d.analysis.IAnalysis
public class ShiftedSpikeScatterPlotRunner
extends ScatterPlot
This class contains a runner used to display the 3d embedding of the shifted spike dataset.

Multiple embedding presets can be selected to view different interesting results. These presets are based on different Embedders and Measures.

The dataset in use is generated using ConstructedData.shiftedSpikes(double, double). The parameter values range from -1 to 1. The size of the dataset is just short of 18000 Polygons.

Author:
Anton Ballmaier

      public ShiftedSpikeScatterPlotRunner​(ShiftedSpikeScatterPlotRunner.Preset preset)
      Constructs a new ShiftedSpikeScatterPlotRunner object using the given ShiftedSpikeScatterPlotRunner.Preset for embedding. The point size of the embedded points is fixed to 1.
      Parameters:
      preset - the ShiftedSpikeScatterPlotRunner.Preset defining the Embedder used to generate points from the dataset

  • Method Details

    • main

      public static void main​(java.lang.String[] args)
      Main method making this class a runner for the scatter plot it implements.

      A ShiftedSpikeScatterPlotRunner-Instance is initialized and used to plot the embedding of a generated dataset. The used ShiftedSpikeScatterPlotRunner.Preset can be changed to view the different predefined embedding methods.

      Parameters:
      args - unused

    • getPoints

      protected java.util.List<org.jzy3d.plot3d.primitives.LightPoint> getPoints()
      Returns the set of LightPoints to be plotted. Every LightPoint contains information about the position and the color of a single point.

      The light points are generated by embedding the Polygon dataset using this instances embedding ShiftedSpikeScatterPlotRunner.Preset.
